# Requirements Traceability

When adding or changing behavior:

1. Identify the module (`PLAT`, `INT`, `EDIT`, `CTX`, `DOCS`, `WF`, `AG`, `EXT`, `DEP`, `TOOL`, `KNOW`).
2. Open `.kiro/specs/copilot-plus-extension/requirements/<NN>-<module>.md`.
3. Implement acceptance criteria verbatim; add `// R-XXX-N` comment at public entry points when non-obvious.
4. Cross-check `.kiro/specs/copilot-plus-extension/requirements.md` Cross-Reference Index for dependencies.

## Test mapping

Integration tests should name cases after requirements: `test('R-PLAT-2.2 shows sign-in when no copilot model', ...)`.

## Do not

- Implement features not in the spec without updating the spec first.
- Weaken EARS criteria (SHALL/MUST) silently.
